<div id="review_3334879446" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3334879446" />
    <a title="Baba" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60866073-baba"><img alt="Baba" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532961539p2/60866073.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3334879446?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Baba" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Baba" href="/user/show/60866073-baba">Baba</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781407230085" href="/book/show/13629345-the-forever-war">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/60866073-baba?shelf=sfmasterworks">sfmasterworks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/60866073-baba?shelf=scifi">scifi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/60866073-baba?shelf=this-book-tho">this-book-tho</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3334879446" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2732475843221504906"><b>SF Masterworks 1(!)</b>. That&apos;s right, this book was the first released under the SF Masterworks brand, so it&apos;s gotta be good then? It sure damn was! This book!<br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1496612875ra/22933780.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>A star gate like natural phenomena has been discovered that allows man to roam the stars - but each journey albeit instantaneous seems and equivalent amount if time will have passed on Earth. As the UN-led Erath ratchets up space colonisation, aliens, the Taurans, destroyed Earth ships, thus sparking a war, a war that goes on for ever!<br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1589404005ra/29470056.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Enforce</span>
  <span id="freeText2732475843221504906" style="display:none"><b>SF Masterworks 1(!)</b>. That's right, this book was the first released under the SF Masterworks brand, so it's gotta be good then? It sure damn was! This book!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1496612875ra/22933780.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>A star gate like natural phenomena has been discovered that allows man to roam the stars - but each journey albeit instantaneous seems and equivalent amount if time will have passed on Earth. As the UN-led Erath ratchets up space colonisation, aliens, the Taurans, destroyed Earth ships, thus sparking a war, a war that goes on for ever!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1589404005ra/29470056.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Enforced conscription of the best and bravest, sees first person narrator, and at heart pacifist William Mandella share his war career in this book. Haldeman, already strikes gold, by using an emotionally intelligent pacifist, but assured veteran to narrate the story. He provides a very realistic (like BSG 2004, style) approach to space combat and colonisation.<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1614914552i/30964427._SX540_.png" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>He uses the passage of time to give a background story of the development of an Earth and colonies under an ongoing universally war state. What he does most of all though, is tell a hugely important story from a very human angle, and tell it really well. Goddamn Five Star read!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1589404005ra/29470058.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>And to top all this off... what a fabulous ending! It will come as no surprise that this was written as a reaction to America's war in Vietnam. So that's it then, this is currently the best sci-fi book I have ever read! <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/12476.Joe_Haldeman" title="Joe Haldeman" rel="nofollow noopener">Joe Haldeman</a> I salute you sir, 10 out of 12, Five Star Read.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1597556549ra/29974391.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="2732475843221504906" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


